   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF THE MINOR PROPHETS MESSAGE FOUR ON HOSEA 3 THE SINS OF THE APOSTATE PEOPLE,</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE PUNISHMENTS OF JEHOVAH,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>AND</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>THE RETURN OF THE APOSTATE PEOPLE Scripture Reading: Hosea 4 6</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Hosea 4 6 covers the sins of the apostate people, the punishments of Jehovah, and the return of the apostate people.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In this message we will consider the details regarding these matters recorded in these three chapters.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>I. THE SINS OF THE APOSTATE PEOPLE</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>AND THE PUNISHMENTS OF JEHOVAH</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The sins of the apostate people and the punishments of Jehovah are seen in 4:1 5:14 and 6:4-10.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>A. The Sins of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>and the Punishments of Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>concerning the People in General 1.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>No Faithfulness, No Kindness,</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>and No Knowledge of God</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Hosea 4:1 tells us that Jehovah had a controversy with the inhabitants of the land, for there were no faithfulness or truth, no kindness, and no knowledge of God.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>False Swearing, Deceiving, Murder,</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Stealing, and Adultery</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Instead of truth, kindness, and the knowledge of God, there were false swearing, deceiving not fulfilling one s promise , murder, stealing, and adultery v. 2a .</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The People Being Violent</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The people were violent, and bloodshed followed bloodshed v. 2b .</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The Land Mourning,</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>and the Inhabitants of the Land Languishing</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Because of this the land mourned, and the inhabitants of the land languished with the beasts of the field and with the birds of heaven.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Indeed, even the fish of the sea would be taken away v. 3 .</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>B. The Sins of the People</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>and the Punishments of Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>concerning the Priests 1.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>The People Contending with the Priest</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>The people contended with the priest v. 4 . This was altogether contrary to God s law, which did not allow the people to contend with the priests.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>The Priest Stumbling in the Day,</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>and the Prophet Stumbling</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>with the Priest in the Night</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Verse 5 says that the priest would stumble in the day and that the prophet would stumble with the priest in the night.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Also, the mother of the priest would be destroyed by God.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>This tells us that they all were committing sins.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>The prophet cooperated with the priest to commit sin, and the mother of the priest joined them.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>That brought in God s judgment upon the mother.</S>
   </TEXT>
